cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.SI 

The paper discusses adversarial attacks and defenses for graph deep learning models, which are commonly used in tasks such as node classification and graph classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of integrated gradients, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the proposed defense approach involves statistical analysis of the graph data, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
